                                <div class="part-2-content" id="part-3-text">
                                    <p>This is a branding project I am currently working on for Republic Bank. I chose
                                        the reverse figure ground of the “R” and the “B” because I wanted something bold
                                        that would show the hierarchy of the letters without trying too hard. Choosing
                                        the color palette was a challenge at first but I decided to lean into the red,
                                        white and blue because of the bank’s name, a “republic” being a form of
                                        government and the bank being in America. I knew it made the most sense and
                                        looked great on paper. I have designed the business cards, stationery, envelope
                                        and other smaller applications so far but still have a ways to go. I am proud of
                                        my work thus far and can’t wait to finish the project! </p>
